{"id":75831,"date":"2022-04-14T10:56:02","date_gmt":"2022-04-14T09:56:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=75831"},"modified":"2022-07-19T10:26:57","modified_gmt":"2022-07-19T08:26:57","slug":"rio-celeste-waterfalls","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/rio-celeste-waterfalls\/","title":{"rendered":"Rio Celeste Waterfalls, Costa Rica: The Ultimate Visitors Guide"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-tenorio-volcano-national-park\">Tenorio Volcano National Park<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tenorio Volcano National Park sits in the beautiful Guanacaste mountain range north of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Costa Rica<\/a>. It&#x2019;s known for its volcano (standing at 6,286 feet tall ~ 1.9 kilometers) and hiking trail, but above all, people visit to see the magic Rio Celeste Waterfalls. The volcano is dormant, but there is still lots of geothermal activity occurring on this site, especially in the river.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/07083631\/rio-celeste-2.jpg\" alt=\"rio celeste waterfall hike costa rica\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"rio celeste waterfall hike costa rica\" class=\"wp-image-79465 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/07083631\/rio-celeste-2.jpg 1281w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/07083631\/rio-celeste-2-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/07083631\/rio-celeste-2-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/0708